Piano voicings that keep the same hand shapes (right hand barely moves)

Use these exact four-note shapes so the top line walks smoothly and that last-bar change is literally one finger.

  • F(add4)/A: LH = A RH = CFAB

  • Am(add4)/C: LH = C RH = CEAD

  • B(add2) (option 1): LH = B RH = BDFC

  • Bm(add2) (option 2): LH = B RH = BDFC

  • F (resolution): LH = F RH = ACFA

  • Dmin (verse cadence): LH = D RH = ACDF

  • C (final): LH = C RH = GCEG

  • F (chorus cadence): LH = F RH = ACFA C as above

Why this works: the top voice traces B D (C or C) A (F or E) G, a natural walk, while the bass outlines your inversions (A C B F D or F C). The only verse/chorus difference is that penultimate bar (Dmin vs F) before Ctotally a one-finger move.

Nashville (for capo/transposing): I(add4)/3 vi(add4)/1 IV(add2) [or iv(add2)] I (vi V) [verse] or (I V) [chorus]

from ai_song_maker import song_maker

def render_sample(abc_str, midi_path, xml_path):
    ordered_part_instrument = {
        'Piano': 'Acoustic Grand Piano',
    }
    parts_data, score_data = song_maker.process_abc(
        abc_str,
        ordered_part_instrument,
        xml_path,
        midi_path
    )
    return midi_path, xml_path

# Common header
header = """M:4/4
L:1/4
Q:1/4=84
K:F
V:1 clef=treble name="Piano"
"""

# Building blocks (each bar sustains one 4-beat chord)
# Notation uses K:F (Bb in key by default). Lowercase = above middle C; comma lowers octave.
bar1 = "[A, C F b]4"   # F(add4)/A  -> A bass; C F Bb on top
bar2 = "[C E A d]4"    # Am(add4)/C -> C bass; E A D on top
bar3_Bb  = "[B, D F c]4"   # Bb(add2) -> Bb bass; D F C
bar3_Bbm = "[B, _D F c]4"  # Bbm(add2) -> Bb bass; Db F C
bar4 = "[F, A C f]4"   # F
bar7_verse  = "[D, A D f]4"  # Dm
bar7_chorus = "[F, A C f]4"  # F (chorus cadence)
bar8 = "[C, G C e]4"   # C

# Assemble patterns
def assemble_sequence(use_bbm=False, cadence="verse"):

# Analyze the uploaded MIDI: /mnt/data/FlickerDemo2.mid
# We'll extract: duration, parts, time signatures, tempo marks, key guess, and a rough chord-per-measure table.
# We'll also convert the MIDI to ABC text for transparency/reference.

%run /mnt/data/add_song_maker_py
from ai_song_maker import song_maker

from music21 import converter, tempo, meter, key, chord, note, stream

midi_path = "/mnt/data/FlickerDemo2.mid"

score = converter.parse(midi_path)

# --- Basic metadata
# Duration (seconds) estimate via highest offset
duration_quarters = score.highestTime
# Try to find initial tempo
tempos = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark))
time_sigs = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature))
keys = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(key.Key))

# Build tempo map (offset in quarters, bpm)
tempo_rows = []
for mm in tempos:
    tempo_rows.append({"offset_quarters": float(mm.offset), "bpm": mm.number})

# Build time signature map
ts_rows = []
for ts in time_sigs:
    ts_rows.append({"offset_quarters": float(ts.offset), "time_signature": ts.ratioString})

# Key guess: take the first explicit key if present, else use analysis
if keys:
    key_guess = keys[0].tonic.name + " " + keys[0].mode
else:
    # Try music21 analysis
    key_guess = score.analyze('key').tonic.name + " " + score.analyze('key').mode

# --- Rough chord per measure (very approximate)
# We chordify, then inside each measure take the longest-sounding chord symbol.
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures()  # split into measures
rows = []
for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
    # find the "heaviest" chord in this measure by duration
    best = None
    best_dur = 0.0
    for el in m.recurse().notesAndRests:
        if isinstance(el, chord.Chord):
            dur = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
            if dur > best_dur:
                best_dur = dur
                best = el
    if best is not None:
        # chord symbol-ish text
        rn = None
        try:
            # roman numeral (needs a key)
            ks = score.analyze('key')
            rn = ks.romanNumeralFromChord(best).figure
        except Exception:
            rn = None
        rows.append({
            "measure": m.number,
            "start_quarter_offset": float(m.offset) if m.offset is not None else None,
            "chord_pitches": " ".join(p.nameWithOctave for p in best.pitches),
            "root": best.root().name if hasattr(best, "root") else None,
            "common_name": best.commonName,
            "roman_in_"+key_guess: rn
        })

# Convert to ABC (for transparency / optional editing pipeline)
abc_text = song_maker.score_to_abc(score)
abc_path = "/mnt/data/FlickerDemo2_ABC.txt"
with open(abc_path, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    f.write(abc_text)

# Present small summaries
from caas_jupyter_tools import display_dataframe_to_user
import pandas as pd

tempo_df = pd.DataFrame(tempo_rows) if tempo_rows else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No explicit tempo marks found"}])
ts_df = pd.DataFrame(ts_rows) if ts_rows else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No explicit time signatures found"}])
chords_df = pd.DataFrame(rows)

display_dataframe_to_user("FlickerDemo2 - Tempo Map", tempo_df)
display_dataframe_to_user("FlickerDemo2 - Time Signatures", ts_df)
display_dataframe_to_user("FlickerDemo2 - Rough Chord-Per-Measure (approx.)", chords_df)

print("SUMMARY")
print("Parts:", len(score.parts))
print("Estimated Key:", key_guess)
print("Duration (quarters):", duration_quarters)
print("Saved ABC to:", abc_path)

from ai_song_maker import song_maker
from music21 import converter, tempo, meter, key, chord, stream

midi_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid"
score = converter.parse(midi_path)

duration_quarters = score.highestTime
tempos = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark))
time_sigs = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature))
keys = list(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(key.Key))

tempo_rows = [{"offset_quarters": float(mm.offset), "bpm": mm.number} for mm in tempos]
ts_rows = [{"offset_quarters": float(ts.offset), "time_signature": ts.ratioString} for ts in time_sigs]

if keys:
    key_guess = keys[0].tonic.name + " " + keys[0].mode
else:
    k = score.analyze('key')
    key_guess = k.tonic.name + " " + k.mode

# Rough chord per measure via chordify (approximate)
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures()

rows = []
for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
    best = None
    best_dur = 0.0
    for el in m.recurse().getElementsByClass(chord.Chord):
        dur = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
        if dur > best_dur:
            best_dur = dur
            best = el
    if best is not None:
        try:
            ks = score.analyze('key')
            rn = ks.romanNumeralFromChord(best).figure
        except Exception:
            rn = None
        rows.append({
            "measure": m.number,
            "start_quarter_offset": float(m.offset) if m.offset is not None else None,
            "chord_pitches": " ".join(p.nameWithOctave for p in best.pitches),
            "root": best.root().name if hasattr(best, "root") else None,
            "common_name": best.commonName,
            "roman_in_"+key_guess: rn
        })

# Save ABC conversion for transparency
abc_text = song_maker.score_to_abc(score)
abc_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover_ABC.txt"
with open(abc_path, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    f.write(abc_text)

from caas_jupyter_tools import display_dataframe_to_user
import pandas as pd

tempo_df = pd.DataFrame(tempo_rows) if tempo_rows else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No explicit tempo marks found"}])
ts_df = pd.DataFrame(ts_rows) if ts_rows else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No explicit time signatures found"}])
chords_df = pd.DataFrame(rows) if rows else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"Chord summary not available (very sparse or monophonic MIDI)"}])

display_dataframe_to_user("TrueBelieverCover - Tempo Map", tempo_df)
display_dataframe_to_user("TrueBelieverCover - Time Signatures", ts_df)
display_dataframe_to_user("TrueBelieverCover - Rough Chord-Per-Measure (approx.)", chords_df)

print("SUMMARY")
print("Parts:", len(score.parts))
print("Estimated Key:", key_guess)
print("Duration (quarters):", duration_quarters)
print("Saved ABC to:", abc_path)

Pad (warm/airy, super low in the mix)

Bass (root-first, tasteful pickups)

  • If a bar ends on the dominant, walk 51 into the downbeat.

Drum lift (add later or keep for Video #3)

  • 4/4 pocket: kick on 1/3, snare 2/4, hats 8ths; add a pre-chorus 1-bar snare roll (low velocity ramp).

Vocals: make them sound expensive with what you have

Room = 80% of the sound. Quick hack stack (10 minutes):

  • Hang a blanket/duvet behind you and to your left/right (dead the first reflections).

  • Face a corner with your mic 1218 in (3045 cm) from your mouth, pop filter at ~2 in.

  • Aim input so peaks hit 12 dBFS (plenty of headroom).

One-click starter chain (any DAW, stock plugins OK):

  1. HPF at 80100 Hz (gentle slope).

  2. Compressor 3:1, attack 2535 ms, release 80120 ms, aim 36 dB GR on loud phrases.

  3. De-esser around 67 kHz (only when it bites).

  4. EQ sweeten: tiny 2 dB @ 300 Hz if muddy; +12 dB shelf @ 810 kHz for air.

  5. Plate verb (1.62.0 s) on a send at 18 to 22 dB; Slap delay 90120 ms very low (optional).

Comping workflow (fast & kind):

  • Record 2 full passes.

  • Swipe-comp best phrases; dont over-edit; tune only obvious misses.

  • Print Lead, Double (low) at 12 dB, Double (high) at 15 dB for thickness.

Image & on-camera comfort (no self-drag, all signal)

  • Light high + 45 (lamp or window), camera at eye level or slightly above.

  • Solid top, simple background; a tiny hair/face light if possible.

  • Keep one consistent look across 35 posts; let the music be the variable.

  • Filters are tools; use subtle ones that dont shift your skin tone or distract.

# Build a "barely-there" PAD track that follows your TrueBelieverCover.mid harmony per measure.
# It chordifies your MIDI, takes each measure's main chord root, and creates a soft pad voicing: 159 (no third).
# Exports a single-track MIDI you can drop under your performance.

from music21 import converter, chord, stream, note, instrument, meter, tempo

src_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid"
pad_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad.mid"
xml_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad.musicxml"

# Load your MIDI
score = converter.parse(src_path)

# Make sure we have measures to align to
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures(inPlace=False)

# Create pad stream
pad_stream = stream.Stream()
pad_stream.append(instrument.SynthStrings1())
# Copy over first tempo mark and time signature if found
mm = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
if mm:
    pad_stream.append(mm)
ts = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
if ts:
    pad_stream.append(ts)

def quantize_to_mid3(p):
    # keep pad in a comfy C3C4 band
    while p.midi < 48:  # below C3
        p = p.transpose(12)
    while p.midi > 60:  # above C4
        p = p.transpose(-12)
    return p

# Build a pad chord per measure using the longest chord in that bar
for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
    best = None
    best_dur = 0.0
    for el in m.recurse().getElementsByClass(chord.Chord):
        dur = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
        if dur > best_dur:
            best_dur = dur
            best = el
    dur = m.duration.quarterLength if m.duration else best_dur if best_dur > 0 else 4.0
    if best is None:
        # rest measure
        r = note.Rest(quarterLength=dur)
        pad_stream.append(r)
        continue

    root_pitch = best.root()  # music21 pitch
    root_pitch = quantize_to_mid3(root_pitch)

    fifth = root_pitch.transpose(7)
    ninth = root_pitch.transpose(14)  # add9
    # Build the pad chord (omit 3rd to avoid clashes with your piano)
    pad_ch = chord.Chord([root_pitch, fifth, ninth])
    pad_ch.duration.quarterLength = dur
    # very soft velocity via style (some DAWs honor; otherwise adjust track gain in DAW)
    try:
        pad_ch.volume.velocity = 36
    except Exception:
        pass
    pad_stream.append(pad_ch)

# Export
pad_stream.write('midi', fp=pad_path)
pad_stream.write('musicxml', fp=xml_path)

print("Exported pad files:")
print(pad_path)
print(xml_path)

    root_pitch = quantize_to_mid3(best.root())

    except Exception:

How its built: per measure, it takes the chords root, adds fifth (+7) and add9 (+14), and omits the 3rd so it never fights your piano. It sits in the C3C4 register (warm, not boomy).

how to set it so its almost not there

  1. Instrument: pick a pad/synth strings (Warm Pad/Synth Strings).

  2. EQ: HPF 120 Hz, LPF 68 kHz (pads dont need sparkle).

  3. Reverb (send): small plate/hall 1.62.2 s, send around 20 dB.

  4. Level: pull the PAD fader all the way down play your section raise slowly until you just notice a change in the air around the piano back off 1 dB.

    • If you mute the pad and the room suddenly feels smaller, you nailed it.

  5. Automation (optional): ramp +1 to +2 dB into the chorus downbeat, then back to baseline.

what to listen for

  • Piano feels wider/deeper without hearing a new instrument.

  • Low mids (200400 Hz) shouldnt thicken too much; if they do, raise HPF to 150180 Hz.

  • If your melody leans on 2nds, the pads add9 will hold the space under it.

# Create two more pad options from the user's TrueBelieverCover.mid
# A = already made: TrueBeliever_Pad.mid (warm, low register, 1-5-9)
# B (High Halo) = octave-up airy pad: 1-5-9 in higher register (C4C5-ish)
# C (Root+5 Glow) = ultra-simple root+fifth only, split into two notes per bar for gentle movement

from music21 import converter, chord, stream, note, instrument, meter, tempo

src_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid"

score = converter.parse(src_path)
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures(inPlace=False)

def first_tempo_and_ts(src):
    mm = next(iter(src.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
    ts = next(iter(src.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
    return mm, ts

def build_pad(measures, register_low=48, register_high=60, use_add9=True, split_halfnotes=False):
    s = stream.Stream()
    s.append(instrument.SynthStrings1())
    mm, ts = first_tempo_and_ts(score)
    if mm: s.append(mm)
    if ts: s.append(ts)

    def clamp_to_register(pitch_obj):
        while pitch_obj.midi < register_low:
            pitch_obj = pitch_obj.transpose(12)
        while pitch_obj.midi > register_high:
            pitch_obj = pitch_obj.transpose(-12)
        return pitch_obj

    for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
        best = None
        best_dur = 0.0
        for el in m.recurse().getElementsByClass(chord.Chord):
            dur = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
            if dur > best_dur:
                best_dur = dur
                best = el
        dur = m.duration.quarterLength if m.duration else best_dur if best_dur > 0 else 4.0
        if best is None:
            s.append(note.Rest(quarterLength=dur))
            continue

        root = clamp_to_register(best.root())
        fifth = root.transpose(7)
        notes = [root, fifth]
        if use_add9:
            ninth = root.transpose(14)
            notes.append(ninth)

        if split_halfnotes and dur >= 4.0:
            # two shorter events for a gentle pulse
            ch1 = chord.Chord(notes)
            ch1.duration.quarterLength = dur/2
            ch2 = chord.Chord(notes)
            ch2.duration.quarterLength = dur/2
            for ch in (ch1, ch2):
                try:
                    ch.volume.velocity = 36
                except Exception:
                    pass
                s.append(ch)
        else:
            ch = chord.Chord(notes)
            ch.duration.quarterLength = dur
            try:
                ch.volume.velocity = 36
            except Exception:
                pass
            s.append(ch)
    return s

# Build B: High Halo (higher register, add9)
pad_high = build_pad(measures, register_low=60, register_high=72, use_add9=True, split_halfnotes=False)
pad_high_mid = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_High.mid"
pad_high_xml = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_High.musicxml"
pad_high.write('midi', fp=pad_high_mid)
pad_high.write('musicxml', fp=pad_high_xml)

# Generate a "HALO (grit)" pad variant: higher register, gentle half-note movement, slight shimmer (adds octave on top)
# It follows the user's TrueBelieverCover.mid harmony per measure.

from music21 import converter, chord, stream, note, instrument, meter, tempo

src_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid"
pad_mid = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_HaloGrit.mid"
pad_xml = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_HaloGrit.musicxml"

score = converter.parse(src_path)
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures(inPlace=False)

s = stream.Stream()
s.append(instrument.SynthStrings1())
mm = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
ts = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
if mm: s.append(mm)
if ts: s.append(ts)

def clamp(p, lo=60, hi=76):  # keep in C4E5 area
    while p.midi < lo:
        p = p.transpose(12)
    while p.midi > hi:
        p = p.transpose(-12)
    return p

for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
    # pick the longest chord in the bar
    best, best_dur = None, 0.0
    for el in m.recurse().getElementsByClass(chord.Chord):
        d = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
        if d > best_dur:
            best_dur = d
            best = el
    dur = m.duration.quarterLength if m.duration else best_dur if best_dur > 0 else 4.0
    if best is None:
        s.append(note.Rest(quarterLength=dur))
        continue

    root = clamp(best.root())
    fifth = clamp(root.transpose(7))
    ninth = clamp(root.transpose(14))
    # shimmer: very light upper octave of the ninth (quiet)
    ninth8 = clamp(ninth.transpose(12))

    # make two half-bar events for a subtle breathe/pulse
    half = max(1.0, dur/2.0)
    ch1 = chord.Chord([root, fifth, ninth, ninth8])
    ch1.duration.quarterLength = half
    ch2 = chord.Chord([root, fifth, ninth, ninth8])
    ch2.duration.quarterLength = half

    # set soft velocities
    for ch in (ch1, ch2):
        try:
            ch.volume.velocity = 34
        except Exception:
            pass
        s.append(ch)

s.write('midi', fp=pad_mid)
s.write('musicxml', fp=pad_xml)

print("HALO (grit) pad exported:")
print(pad_mid)
print(pad_xml)

# Create a softer "HALO" pad variant (higher register, very low velocity, sustained per bar)
# Follows the harmony of /mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid measure-by-measure.

%run /mnt/data/add_song_maker_py
from music21 import converter, chord, stream, note, instrument, meter, tempo

src_path = "/mnt/data/TrueBelieverCover.mid"
pad_mid = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_HaloSoft.mid"
pad_xml = "/mnt/data/TrueBeliever_Pad_HaloSoft.musicxml"

score = converter.parse(src_path)
chordified = score.chordify()
measures = chordified.makeMeasures(inPlace=False)

s = stream.Stream()
s.append(instrument.SynthStrings1())  # generic pad instrument tag
mm = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
ts = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
if mm: s.append(mm)
if ts: s.append(ts)

def clamp(p, lo=60, hi=76):  # about C4E5
    while p.midi < lo:
        p = p.transpose(12)
    while p.midi > hi:
        p = p.transpose(-12)
    return p

for m in measures.getElementsByClass(stream.Measure):
    best, best_dur = None, 0.0
    for el in m.recurse().getElementsByClass(chord.Chord):
        d = float(el.duration.quarterLength)
        if d > best_dur:
            best_dur = d
            best = el
    dur = m.duration.quarterLength if m.duration else best_dur if best_dur > 0 else 4.0
    if best is None:
        s.append(note.Rest(quarterLength=dur))
        continue

    root = clamp(best.root())
    fifth = clamp(root.transpose(7))
    ninth = clamp(root.transpose(14))

    ch = chord.Chord([root, fifth, ninth])
    ch.duration.quarterLength = dur
    try:
        ch.volume.velocity = 22  # very soft
    except Exception:
        pass
    s.append(ch)

s.write('midi', fp=pad_mid)
s.write('musicxml', fp=pad_xml)

print("OK")
print(pad_mid)
print(pad_xml)

# Create 3 simple drum MIDI building blocks you can drag anywhere in your session.
# A) Verse Pulse (subtle)  4 bars
# B) Chorus Groove (pocket)  4 bars
# C) 1-bar Lift (pre-chorus roll)

%run /mnt/data/add_song_maker_py
from music21 import stream, tempo, meter, instrument, note, midi

def make_track(bpm=84, bars=4, kind='verse'):
    s = stream.Stream()
    s.append(tempo.MetronomeMark(number=bpm))
    s.append(meter.TimeSignature('4/4'))
    s.append(instrument.Woodblock())  # tag as unpitched; GM kits will still map by note numbers
    
    # GM note numbers
    KICK = 36
    SNARE = 38
    HAT_C = 42
    SHAKER = 82
    CRASH = 49
    
    q = 1.0  # quarter length
    for b in range(bars):
        bar_offset = b*4*q
        
        if kind == 'verse':
            # Very light: shaker 8ths, kick on 1, snare light on 4
            for i in range(8):  # 8ths
                n = note.Note(SHAKER)
                n.duration.quarterLength = 0.5
                n.volume.velocity = 28
                s.insert(bar_offset + i*0.5*q, n)
            # kick beat 1
            k = note.Note(KICK); k.duration.quarterLength = 1.0; k.volume.velocity = 50
            s.insert(bar_offset + 0*q, k)
            # light snare beat 4
            sn = note.Note(SNARE); sn.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; sn.volume.velocity = 38
            s.insert(bar_offset + 3*q, sn)
        
        elif kind == 'chorus':
            # Pocket: kick on 1 & 3 (+ light anticipations), snare 2 & 4, hats 8ths
            for i in range(8):  # hats
                h = note.Note(HAT_C)
                h.duration.quarterLength = 0.5
                h.volume.velocity = 44 if i%2==0 else 34  # slight open/close feel
                s.insert(bar_offset + i*0.5*q, h)
            # kick 1 & 3
            for bt in [0, 2]:
                k = note.Note(KICK); k.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; k.volume.velocity = 64
                s.insert(bar_offset + bt*q, k)
            # ghost kick before 1 of next bar (on 4-and)
            if b < bars-1:
                gk = note.Note(KICK); gk.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; gk.volume.velocity = 40
                s.insert(bar_offset + 3.5*q, gk)
            # snare 2 & 4
            for bt in [1, 3]:
                sn = note.Note(SNARE); sn.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; sn.volume.velocity = 70
                s.insert(bar_offset + bt*q, sn)
            # light crash on first downbeat of bar 1 only
            if b == 0:
                c = note.Note(CRASH); c.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; c.volume.velocity = 72
                s.insert(bar_offset + 0*q, c)
        
        elif kind == 'lift':
            # 1-bar snare roll crescendo, hat 8ths, crash at downbeat
            for i in range(8):  # hats 8ths
                h = note.Note(HAT_C); h.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; h.volume.velocity = 36
                s.insert(bar_offset + i*0.5*q, h)
            # 16th snare rolls across bar with rising velocity
            for i in range(16):
                sn = note.Note(SNARE)
                sn.duration.quarterLength = 0.25
                sn.volume.velocity = 36 + int(i*(72-36)/15)
                s.insert(bar_offset + i*0.25*q, sn)
            # crash lands at NEXT bar's 1 (export as an extra note at end)
            c = note.Note(CRASH); c.duration.quarterLength = 0.5; c.volume.velocity = 80
            s.insert(bar_offset + 4*q, c)
    
    # Force channel 10 (drums) in MIDI file
    mf = midi.translate.streamToMidiFile(s)
    for track in mf.tracks:
        for ev in track.events:
            if hasattr(ev, 'channel'):
                ev.channel = 9  # 0-based, channel 10
    return mf

            for bt in [1,3]:
                sn=note.Note(SNARE); sn.duration.quarterLength=0.5; sn.volume.velocity=70; s.insert(bar + bt*q, sn)
            if b==0:
                c=note.Note(CR); c.duration.quarterLength=0.5; c.volume.velocity=72; s.insert(bar + 0*q, c)
        elif kind=='lift':
            for i in range(8):
                h=note.Note(HAT); h.duration.quarterLength=0.5; h.volume.velocity=36; s.insert(bar + i*0.5*q, h)
            for i in range(16):
                sn=note.Note(SNARE); sn.duration.quarterLength=0.25; sn.volume.velocity=36 + int(i*(72-36)/15); s.insert(bar + i*0.25*q, sn)
            c=note.Note(CR); c.duration.quarterLength=0.5; c.volume.velocity=80; s.insert(bar + 4*q, c)
    mf = midi.translate.streamToMidiFile(s)
    for tr in mf.tracks:
        for ev in tr.events:
            if hasattr(ev, 'channel'):
                ev.channel = 9
    return mf

totallylets do a tiny, neurodivergent-friendly drum mini-lesson using your song as the canvas. no jargon, one layer at a time, with pictures-in-your-head you can feel.

0) the movie-in-your-chest analogy

  • Kick = heartbeat. It says were alive and outlines your chord roots.

  • Snare = punctuation. Like a period or exclamationwhere the line lands.

  • Hi-hat/shaker = air. The whoosh between wordsthe fabric that keeps it moving.

  • Cymbals = scene cuts. A crash = new scene (versechorus).

If you remember nothing else: heart hands air scene cut.

1) tempo = walking pace for the whole band

Pick one steady walk. Count out loud:

1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & (those & are the little steps in between)

  • The numbers are strong steps.

  • The &s are tiny steps between.

Thats your grid. Well hang everything on it.

2) verse pulse (quiet heartbeat)

Think of a dim room, candle on.

  • Air (shaker/hat): whisper ts on every &
    Count: 1 _ & _ 2 _ & _ 3 _ & _ 4 _ & _

  • Heart (kick): a soft bump on 1

  • Punctuation (snare): a tap at 4 (like inhaling to speak)

It feels like: heart (breathe) speak
Minimal, intimate. This is why verses feel close.

Body exercise:
Stomp (kick) on 1, clap (snare) on 4, hiss ts on every &. Do 4 bars.

3) pre-chorus lift (tightening the spring)

Same room, someone turns the dimmer up.

  • Keep the air going.

  • Add a gentle snare build across one bar (little taps getting slightly stronger).

  • Land a crash right on the next 1 (new scene!).

Think: holding breath exhale on the downbeat.

4) chorus pocket (clear punctuation, bigger steps)

Lights up. Keep it simple, confident.

  • Air (hi-hat): every & (steady).

  • Heart (kick): 1 and 3 (sometimes a tiny pickup on 4&).

  • Punctuation (snare): 2 and 4 (this is the classic backbeat).

Count one bar:

Kick on 1 Snare on 2 Kick on 3 Snare on 4
Hats (air) on all the **&**s.

Body exercise:
Stomp on 1 & 3, clap on 2 & 4, nod on every &. Feels like walking with swagger.

5) dynamics = whisper / speak / shout

Forget numbers. Use words:

  • Whisper = verse hats/shaker and gentle kick.

  • Speak = chorus hats, normal snare.

  • Shout = only for crashes and tiny fill moments.

Rule: most of the kit stays in whisper/speak. Shout is rare (so it matters).

6) tiny spices (when youre ready)

  • Ghost notes: feather-light snare taps between 2 and 4 (like breathing).

  • Anticipation: a quick kick on 4& that leads into 1 (feels exciting).

  • Human feel: nudge a few hats a hair late/early so its not robotic. (Trust ears: if it wiggles nicely, keep it.)

7) one-DAW step you can do right now (no overwhelm)

Make three MIDI tracks: HAT/SHKR, KICK, SNARE. Then:

Verse (2 bars to loop)

  • HAT/SHKR: put notes on every & (8 notes per bar).

  • KICK: one soft note on 1.

  • SNARE: one soft note on 4.

Pre-chorus (1 bar)

  • Keep hats. On SNARE: 16 little taps that get slightly stronger.

  • Place a CRASH right on the next bars 1.

Chorus (2 bars to loop)

  • HAT: every &.

  • KICK: 1 and 3 (+ optional 4& pickup).

  • SNARE: 2 and 4.

Thats it. Youve built the whole arc.

  • If your strings enter earlier, keep drums whisper-level so they dont crowd the vocal.

you did it right: you zoomed in and the 1/32 grid showed up. thats exactly what we need for the little snare roll.

quick vocab (tiny + friendly)

  • Bar / Measure = a box of time. In 4/4, each bar has 4 beats.

  • Beat = the footstep (count 1 2 3 4).

  • Subdivision = tiny steps inside a beat.

    • 1/8 say 1 & 2 & (2 per beat)

    • 1/16 1 e & a (4 per beat)

    • 1/32 split each of those in half (8 per beat)

  • Backbeat = the strong snare on 2 and 4.

  • Tick (casual) = a grid slot. (In MIDI-speak, ticks are the tiny internal units, but you can ignore that.)

So when you say the tick I had on 1 now covers four smaller ones, you just zoomed from a coarser grid to a finer one. Totally normal.

Drums tip: for most kits, note length doesnt matter, only where you place the hit. Keep drum notes short so the view stays tidy.

heres a tiny, surgical tidy so it feels right and stops overpowering:

# Analyze user's uploaded drum MIDI and generate a 2-bar "full+short roll" template
# that matches the file's tempo/time signature. Also report where snare accents land.

%run /mnt/data/add_song_maker_py
from music21 import converter, tempo, meter, instrument, note, midi, stream, meter
import pandas as pd
from caas_jupyter_tools import display_dataframe_to_user

src = "/mnt/data/TBDK1.MID"
score = converter.parse(src)

# Find global tempo & time signature (fallbacks if missing)
mm = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
ts = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
bpm = int(mm.number) if (mm and mm.number) else 84
ts_str = ts.ratioString if ts else "4/4"

# Collect all Note/Unpitched events with channel/note info if possible
rows = []
for p_i, p in enumerate(score.parts):
    pname = getattr(p, 'partName', f'Part {p_i+1}') or f'Part {p_i+1}'
    for n in p.recurse().notes:
        pitch_num = None
        try:
            pitch_num = n.pitch.midi
        except Exception:
            try:
                pitch_num = int(n.pitch.ps)
            except Exception:
                pass
        rows.append({
            "Part": pname,
            "Offset_quarters": float(n.offset),
            "QL": float(n.quarterLength),
            "Velocity": getattr(getattr(n, 'volume', None), 'velocity', None),
            "PitchNum": pitch_num
        })

df = pd.DataFrame(rows).sort_values(["Offset_quarters","Part"]).reset_index(drop=True)
display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  MIDI Events (sorted by time)", df if len(df) else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No notes found"}]))

# Heuristic: classify common GM drum pitches to names
gm_names = {
    35: "Kick (Acoustic)",
    36: "Kick",
    37: "Side Stick (Rim)",
    38: "Snare",
    40: "Snare (Alt)",
    42: "Hi-hat Closed",
    44: "Hi-hat Pedal",
    46: "Hi-hat Open",
    49: "Crash 1",
    51: "Ride 1",
    57: "Crash 2",
    82: "Shaker"
}
if len(df):
    df2 = df.copy()
    df2["GM_Name"] = df2["PitchNum"].map(gm_names).fillna("Other/Unknown")
    display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  GM Drum Guess", df2)

# Try to detect if accents (snare 38/40) land around beats 2 and 4
# We'll assume 4/4; compute position within bar (0..4)
def barpos(offset_ql, ts_str="4/4"):
    beats = int(ts_str.split('/')[0]) if '/' in ts_str else 4
    return offset_ql % beats

accent_rows = []
if len(df):
    for _, r in df.iterrows():
        if r["PitchNum"] in (38,40):  # snares
            pos = barpos(r["Offset_quarters"], ts_str)
            accent_rows.append({"Offset_quarters": r["Offset_quarters"],
                                "BarPos_beats": round(pos, 3),
                                "Velocity": r["Velocity"]})
accent_df = pd.DataFrame(accent_rows).sort_values("Offset_quarters")
display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  Snare Positions (bar-relative)", accent_df if len(accent_rows) else pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No snares detected (38/40)."}]))

# Build a 2-bar "Full + Short roll" template at detected bpm/ts
s = stream.Stream()
s.append(tempo.MetronomeMark(number=bpm))
s.append(meter.TimeSignature(ts_str))

# Use two instruments (tracks) for clarity
pad_side = stream.Part(); pad_side.id = "SideStick"; pad_side.append(instrument.Woodblock())
pad_sn = stream.Part(); pad_sn.id = "Snare"; pad_sn.append(instrument.Woodblock())
pad_kick = stream.Part(); pad_kick.id = "Kick"; pad_kick.append(instrument.Woodblock())

# Constants
q = 1.0
# Pitches
SIDE, SNARE, KICK = 37, 38, 36

# Bar 1: Full roll 12 (six 1/32 taps), accent on 2; Short roll 34 (three 1/16 taps), accent on 4
# Leave a tiny breath after 1 and 3.
# 12 full roll (six 1/32 taps)
start = 0.0 + 0.125  # breath = 1/32*1? here using 1/8 of a beat (i.e., 0.125 quarters)
step32 = 0.125  # 1/32 note = 0.125 quarterLength
vels_full = [24, 26, 28, 30, 33, 36]  # whisper  medium
for i,v in enumerate(vels_full):
    n = note.Note(SIDE); n.duration.quarterLength = step32; n.volume.velocity = v
    pad_side.insert(start + i*step32, n)
# Accent on 2
n2 = note.Note(SNARE); n2.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; n2.volume.velocity = 78
pad_sn.insert(2.0, n2)

# 34 short roll (three 1/16 taps)
start = 3.0 - 0.75  # start at 3e (0.25+0.25+0.25 before 4)
step16 = 0.25
vels_short = [28, 32, 36]
for i,v in enumerate(vels_short):
    n = note.Note(SIDE); n.duration.quarterLength = step16; n.volume.velocity = v
    pad_side.insert(start + i*step16, n)
# Accent on 4
n4 = note.Note(SNARE); n4.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; n4.volume.velocity = 78
pad_sn.insert(4.0, n4)

# Kicks: soft on 1, solid on 3 (optional 4& ghost commented out)
k1 = note.Note(KICK); k1.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; k1.volume.velocity = 46
pad_kick.insert(0.0, k1)
k3 = note.Note(KICK); k3.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; k3.volume.velocity = 62
pad_kick.insert(3.0, k3)
# ghost on 4& (very soft). Uncomment if desired:
#g = note.Note(KICK); g.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; g.volume.velocity = 34
#pad_kick.insert(4.5, g)

# Copy the bar once more (bar 2 identical to bar 1)
for el in pad_side.recurse().notes:
    pad_side.insert(el.offset + 4.0, el.flat.getElementAtOrBefore(el.offset).clone() if hasattr(el, 'clone') else el.__class__(el))
for el in pad_sn.recurse().notes:
    pad_sn.insert(el.offset + 4.0, el.flat.getElementAtOrBefore(el.offset).clone() if hasattr(el, 'clone') else el.__class__(el))
for el in pad_kick.recurse().notes:
    pad_kick.insert(el.offset + 4.0, el.flat.getElementAtOrBefore(el.offset).clone() if hasattr(el, 'clone') else el.__class__(el))

s.insert(0, pad_side)
s.insert(0, pad_sn)
s.insert(0, pad_kick)

out_path = "/mnt/data/SnareRoll_FullShort_Template.mid"
mf = midi.translate.streamToMidiFile(s)
# Force channel 10 for all parts (GM drums)
for tr in mf.tracks:
    for ev in tr.events:
        if hasattr(ev, 'channel'):
            ev.channel = 9
mf.open(out_path, 'wb'); mf.write(); mf.close()

print("Exported:")

from music21 import converter, tempo, meter, note, midi, stream
import pandas as pd
from caas_jupyter_tools import display_dataframe_to_user

src = "/mnt/data/TBDK1.MID"
score = converter.parse(src)

# Tempo / meter
mm = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(tempo.MetronomeMark)), None)
ts = next(iter(score.recurse().getElementsByClass(meter.TimeSignature)), None)
bpm = int(mm.number) if (mm and mm.number) else 84
beats_per_bar = int(ts.numerator) if ts else 4
beat_unit = int(ts.denominator) if ts else 4  # assume 4
ts_str = f"{beats_per_bar}/{beat_unit}"

# Collect note events
rows = []
for p_i, p in enumerate(score.parts):
    pname = getattr(p, 'partName', f'Part {p_i+1}') or f'Part {p_i+1}'
    for n in p.recurse().notes:
        try:
            pitch_num = n.pitch.midi
        except Exception:
            pitch_num = None
        rows.append({
            "Part": pname,
            "Offset_q": float(n.offset),
            "Dur_q": float(n.duration.quarterLength),
            "Vel": getattr(getattr(n, 'volume', None), 'velocity', None),
            "Pitch": pitch_num
        })

df = pd.DataFrame(rows).sort_values("Offset_q").reset_index(drop=True)

def barpos_q(off_q, beats=4):
    return off_q % beats

# Map snares to named 16th slots within the bar
slot_names = {
    0.00: "1",
    0.25: "1e",
    0.50: "1&",
    0.75: "1a",
    1.00: "2",
    1.25: "2e",
    1.50: "2&",
    1.75: "2a",
    2.00: "3",
    2.25: "3e",
    2.50: "3&",
    2.75: "3a",
    3.00: "4",
    3.25: "4e",
    3.50: "4&",
    3.75: "4a",
}
def nearest16th_name(pos):
    # round to nearest 1/4 of a beat (i.e., 16ths in 4/4)
    grid = round(pos*4)/4.0
    grid = max(0.0, min(3.75, grid))  # clamp to [0, 4)
    # snap to two decimals to avoid float issues
    grid = round(grid, 2)
    return slot_names.get(grid, f"{grid:.2f}")

# Filter likely snares (GM 38/40) and side-stick (37)
sn_df = df[df["Pitch"].isin([37,38,40])].copy()
if len(sn_df):
    sn_df["BarPos_q"] = sn_df["Offset_q"].apply(lambda x: barpos_q(x, beats_per_bar))
    sn_df["Nearest16th"] = sn_df["BarPos_q"].apply(nearest16th_name)
    display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  Snare/SideStick Positions", sn_df[["Part","Offset_q","BarPos_q","Nearest16th","Vel","Pitch"]])
    # Summary counts
    summary = (sn_df.groupby(["Nearest16th","Pitch"]).size()
               .reset_index(name="Count")
               .sort_values(["Nearest16th","Pitch"]))
    display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  Snare Slot Summary", summary)
else:
    display_dataframe_to_user("TBDK1  Snare/SideStick Positions", pd.DataFrame([{"info":"No snare/side-stick notes (37/38/40) found."}]))

# ---- Build a 2-bar template with accents on 2& and 4& (no hits on 2e/4e) ----
s = stream.Stream()
s.append(tempo.MetronomeMark(number=bpm))
s.append(meter.TimeSignature(ts_str))

part_side = stream.Part(); part_side.partName = "SideStick (grace)"
part_sn   = stream.Part(); part_sn.partName   = "Snare (accent)"
part_k    = stream.Part(); part_k.partName    = "Kick"

SIDE, SNARE, KICK = 37, 38, 36
q = 1.0

# Helper to add a grace tap 1/32 before the & (no 2e used)
def add_offbeat_accent(bar_start_q, beat_num, grace=True):
    # beat_num is 2 or 4 -> positions are 1.5 and 3.5 within the bar
    and_pos = bar_start_q + (beat_num - 1) + 0.5  # 2&=1.5, 4&=3.5
    if grace:
        # single 1/32 just before the &: 1/32 of a quarter = 0.125 ql before
        g = note.Note(SIDE); g.duration.quarterLength = 0.125; g.volume.velocity = 28
        part_side.insert(and_pos - 0.125, g)  # 1/32 before &
    # accent at &
    acc = note.Note(SNARE); acc.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; acc.volume.velocity = 78
    part_sn.insert(and_pos, acc)

# Bar 1
add_offbeat_accent(0.0, 2, grace=True)  # 2&
add_offbeat_accent(0.0, 4, grace=True)  # 4&
# Kicks: soft 1, solid 3
k1 = note.Note(KICK); k1.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; k1.volume.velocity = 46; part_k.insert(0.0, k1)
k3 = note.Note(KICK); k3.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; k3.volume.velocity = 62; part_k.insert(3.0, k3)

# Bar 2 (repeat)
add_offbeat_accent(4.0, 2, grace=True)
add_offbeat_accent(4.0, 4, grace=True)

k3b = note.Note(KICK); k3b.duration.quarterLength = 0.25; k3b.volume.velocity = 62; part_k.insert(7.0, k3b)

s.insert(0, part_side); s.insert(0, part_sn); s.insert(0, part_k)
